Distribution. U.S.A. (
Summers, 1957 b
;
Summers & Price, 1961
) and Turkey (this paper).

Setae d 2 are located on isolated small shields in the Turkish deutonymphal specimens whereas those of Summers’ ( 1957 b) specimen is on the hysterosomal shield. The presence of discrete lateral shields on the deutonymph shows that these shields incompletely fuse with the median shield after the final moult (
Summers & Price 1961
). Despite the differences in the dorsal shields between the Turkish and U.S.A. deutonymphs, we consider them the same species.

